The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, May 31, 2004  Calcutta Column

	Streetlights at the crossing of JL Nehru Road and SN Banerjee Road are at times not switched off even till 10.30 am. Though the callous power boards are to blame, perhaps, citizens should also be encouraged to lodge complaints whenever they notice such waste. The CESC and WBSEB should take prompt action. 
	Bhupen Bose, Dum Dum. 
	For inexplicable reasons, Baul music hardly features on TV and radio these days. Since the form of music still has a huge following in the state, the cultural department should help revive it. 
	Rabindranath Kar, Sankar Ghosh Lane. 

